# Commits (this repo)

**Normal path:** The user will usually ask you to run **`Commit-AndPush.ps1`** from the repo root with an **appropriate `-CommitMessage`** (summary of what changed and why). That script already runs **`git add -A`** before commit—no need to stage manually unless they say otherwise.

Manual `git add` / partial staging is **rare** here (solo project). If they explicitly ask for scoped staging or a different workflow, follow that.
